We used the Model Genome Interrogator (MGI) tool in PLEXdb (http://www.plexdb.org) to retrieve predicted orthologs between each species and homologous loci in the rice model genome. The MGI matches one or more predicted orthologs to a selected microarray probe-set using GeneSeqer (parameters: −x 12 -y 16 -z 24 -w 0.2) followed by blastx to protein database and blastn to FL-cDNA sequence database (both with E-value < 1e-20), and back, producing a quality score for each pair. To define an injective (one-to-one) orthology between genes, only best alignment score for each probe-set-ortholog hit was considered. Shared DEGs were identified using the penalized Fisher method that combines the P-value distributions from all four species:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
