				\begin{document}$$ {\overline{D}}_g= exp\left(\frac{1}{k}{\displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^klo{g}_e\left({D}_{gi}\right)}\right) $$\end{document}D¯g=exp1k∑i=1klogeDgiwhere D is the expression fold-change of gene g in species i, and k is the number of species from which the average fold-change was calculated.

Measurements of osmotic potential and relative water content (RWC) were conducted on third leaf at mid-day. For osmotic potential analysis, leaves were placed in vials containing double-distilled water and kept in dark cold room for 4 h. Leaves were then dried and frozen in liquid nitrogen. Osmotic potential of the leaf sap was assessed using a vapor pressure osmometer (Vapro5600, Wescor Inc., USA). For RWC analysis, leaves were placed in pre-weighted vials. Vials were immediately weighted to obtain fresh weight (FW) followed by hydration for 6 h to full turgid. Samples were weighted to obtain leaf turgid weight (TW) and then oven dried at 75°C for 72 h to obtain dry weight (DW). RWC was calculated as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
